94. Evaluate the different file handling modes available in PHP with appropriate examples.
•	"r" → Read only
•	"w" → Write (erase old content)
•	"a" → Append (write at end)
•	"x" → Create new file (error if exists)
•	"r+" → Read + Write
•	"w+" → Read + Write (overwrite)
•	"a+" → Read + Write (append)
<?php
// Write Mode
$f = fopen("test.txt", "w");
fwrite($f, "Hello World!");
fclose($f);
// Read Mode
$f = fopen("test.txt", "r");
echo fread($f, filesize("test.txt"));
fclose($f);
?>
